## How to Get Your Notion Token for `.env`

Your token is already inside your MCP config. Locate it at one of these paths:

```
# Claude Desktop MCP config (typical location)
C:\Users\hp\AppData\Roaming\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json

# Or wherever your MCP server is configured
```

Look for the `NOTION_API_KEY` or `NOTION_TOKEN` value inside, and copy it to `.env`:
```
NOTION_DATABASE_ID=abc123def456...   # from browser URL
```
_(Token itself goes in `.env` only if not already resolvable — see parse_config.py design below)_

