### Skills — `skills/`

#### [NEW] `skills/parse_config.py`
- Loads `chromemind.config.yaml`
- Resolves `${ENV_VAR}` placeholders from `.env`
- Validates required fields (database_id, etc.)
- Returns `RunConfig`

#### [NEW] `skills/scrape_bookmarks.py`
Reads Chrome's local `Bookmarks` JSON file:
```
%LOCALAPPDATA%\Google\Chrome\User Data\rohit_essential\Bookmarks
```
- Recursively flattens the nested tree
- Preserves `folder_path` (e.g. `"Dev > Kafka > Articles"`)
- Returns `list[dict]` up to `limit`

#### [NEW] `skills/scrape_history.py` ⭐ _New in v2_
Reads Chrome's `History` SQLite database:
```
%LOCALAPPDATA%\Google\Chrome\User Data\rohit_essential\History
```
- Copies the DB to a temp file first (Chrome locks it when open)
- Queries: `SELECT url, title, visit_count, last_visit_time FROM urls ORDER BY last_visit_time DESC LIMIT ?`
- Converts Chrome's epoch (microseconds since 1601-01-01) to ISO timestamp
- Filters out `chrome://`, `chrome-extension://` internal URLs
- Returns `list[dict]` with `{url, title, visit_count, last_visited_at}`

#### [NEW] `skills/scrape_tabs.py` ⭐ _Chrome DevTools MCP_
Retrieves **active tabs** using Chrome DevTools Protocol:
- Connects to Chrome's remote debugging endpoint: `http://localhost:9222/json`
- Chrome must be started with: `--remote-debugging-port=9222`
- Returns list of `{url, title, tab_group_name}` for all open tabs
- Falls back gracefully if Chrome is not running in debug mode

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Chrome DevTools MCP for Tabs — Setup Required**:
> To scrape active tabs, Chrome must be launched with the remote debugging flag:
> ```bash
> "C:\Program Files\Google\Chrome\Application\chrome.exe" --remote-debugging-port=9222 --profile-directory="rohit_essential"
> ```
> You only need this when running `--source tabs`. Bookmarks and history work without it.

#### [NEW] `skills/normalise_raw_item.py`
- Unified normaliser for all three sources
- Generates `id = sha256(url)` for dedup
- Adds `scraped_at` timestamp
- Sets `source` field: `bookmark | history | tab`
- Handles `visit_count` field (null for bookmarks/tabs)

#### [NEW] `skills/map_to_notion_schema.py`
Maps `RawItem` → Notion page properties. Phase 1 fields:

| RawItem field | Notion property | Type |
|---|---|---|
| `title` | Title | title |
| `url` | URL | url |
| `source` | Source | select |
| `folder_path` | Folder Path | rich_text |
| `scraped_at` | Scraped At | date |
| `id` | ChromeMind ID | rich_text |
| `visit_count` | Visit Count | number |
| _(default)_ | Status | select = "Unread" |

#### [NEW] `skills/notion_upsert.py`
- Queries Notion for existing page by `ChromeMind ID` filter
- If found + `duplicate_strategy=update`: updates non-protected fields
- If found + `duplicate_strategy=skip`: returns `skipped`
- If not found: creates new page
- Short-circuits immediately if `dry_run=True` (just logs)

#### [NEW] `skills/handle_notion_errors.py`
- Wraps SDK calls with retry (1 retry on HTTP 429/500)
- On failure: logs reason, returns `{status: "failed", reason: ...}`
- Never raises — always returns a result dict

#### [NEW] `skills/format_log_entry.py`
Formats log entry as structured JSON: `{agent, event, level, payload, timestamp}`.

#### [NEW] `skills/write_log.py`
- Appends to `logs/chromemind_YYYY-MM-DD.log`
- Log rotation: deletes files older than `retain_days` (default 7)

